channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Democrat Elissa Slotkin, Republican Mike Rogers Win Michigan Primary Races for U.S. Senate
Social media explodes with theory Harris snubbed Gov. Shapiro as VP pick to appease anti-Israel wing of Dems
item.description: Pundits on social media weighed in on VP Harris not selecting PA Gov. Josh Shapiro by saying it shows a problem with antisemitism within the Democratic Party.

item.title: Arizona GOP Elector Loraine Pellegrino Takes False Doc Plea Deal
Say So Long, Squad Member: Cori Bush Loses Her House Seat in Missouri's 1st District (Updated)
Top House Republican from Walz’s home state says ‘radical’ Harris VP pick is 'best' scenario for GOP
item.description: House Majority Whip Tom Emmer spoke with Fox News Digital shortly after Vice President Kamala Harris announced his state's governor will be her running mate.

item.title: 'Squad' Member Cori Bush Loses Primary
item.description: St. Louis County Prosecuting Attorney Wesley Bell has defeated U.S. Rep. Cori Bush in a Democratic primary in St. Louis, marking the second time this year that one of the party's incumbents has been ousted in an expensive contest that reflected deep divisions over the war...

item.title: Kamala Goes Babbling in Philly With Tim Walz, Opens Mouth and Inserts Foot
Obama-linked operatives dominate Harris campaign
item.description: Vice President Harris has hired a handful of senior advisers to her campaign who previously worked on former President Obama's successful campaigns in 2008 and 2012.

item.title: Judge Rules RFK Jr. Can Remain on New Jersey Ballot
item.description: Independent presidential candidate Robert F. Kennedy Jr. will remain on New Jersey's ballot after an administrative law judge found Tuesday that Kennedy had not violated the state's Sore Loser Law, according to the New Jersey Monitor.

item.title: Tim Walz Addresses the Crowd in Philly Following Announcement As VP Pick - I've Got Good News and Bad
Kristen McDonald Privet wins Dem primary for Rep Dan Kildee's open blue Michigan seat
item.description: Kristen McDonald Privet won the Democratic primary in the race to fill Rep. Dan Kildee's D-Mich. seat Tuesday evening.

item.title: MSNBC's Kornacki: Walz Didn't Get Rural Votes in Minn.
item.description: Minnesota Democrat Gov. Tim Walz earned his gubernatorial victory in 2022 using the same playbook as Democrat contenders before him - running up votes in the metropolitan areas but getting scorched in greater Minnesota, according to MSNBC's Steve Kornacki.

item.title: VIDEO: While Minneapolis Burned, Walz's Wife Threw Her Windows Open to Enjoy the Smell of Burning Tires
Paul Junge wins GOP primary for Michigan’s 8th Congressional District
item.description: Paul Junge won the Republican primary in Michigan's 8th Congressional District. He will now look to replace the retiring Dan Kildee.

item.title: Former Kansas AG Wins GOP Primary For Open House Seat
item.description: A former Kansas attorney general and failed candidate for governor has found initial success in his political comeback attempt, winning Tuesday's Republican primary for an open U.S. House seat.
